                    &----------------------------------&
                    &-            PAN EDIT            -&
                    &----------------------------------$

$PAN EDIT ALLOWS YOU TO MORE EASILY USE SPF EDIT TO MODIFY MEMBERS OF
 PANVALET LIBRARIES.

 THE FOLLOWING TOPICS ARE PRESENTED IN SEQUENCE, OR MAY BE SELECTED BY NUMBER:
    &0$- GENERAL INTRODUCTION
    &1$- EDIT PANVALET MEMBER
    &2$- SAVE EDITED MEMBER VIA PAN STORE
    &3$- END PANVALET EDIT STATUS WITHOUT SAVE
    &4$- DISPLAY EDIT STATUS OF PANVALET MEMBER
<ACTION>
1 SELECT CHAR(36) CURSOR;
2 SELECT CHAR(8) LIST(   0   ,   1   ,   2   ,   3   ,   4   )
               RETURN(VTPANE0,VTPANE1,VTPANE2,VTPANE3,VTPANE4);
3 * CHAR(8) INIT('VTPAN   ');
4 * CHAR(8) INIT('VTSUBMT ');
5 * CHAR(8) INIT('VTPANE0 ');
<END>
